Got it 👍 — if you only want operators (no release payload), you can simplify your ImageSetConfiguration a lot.

👉 You do NOT need:

platform section ❌

additionalImages (release images) ❌


👉 You only need:

operators section ✅



---

✅ Minimal Operator-Only ImageSetConfiguration

Use this 👇

apiVersion: mirror.openshift.io/v2alpha1
kind: ImageSetConfiguration

storageConfig:
  registry:
    imageURL: bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4

mirror:
  operators:
    - catalog: registry.redhat.io/redhat/redhat-operator-index:v4.19
      packages:

        # 🔴 ODF FULL STACK (MANDATORY)
        - name: odf-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: ocs-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: odf-csi-addons-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: odf-dependencies
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: mcg-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: cephcsi-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: rook-ceph-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: odf-prometheus-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: recipe
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        # 🟢 OTHER OPERATORS
        - name: local-storage-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable

        - name: kubernetes-nmstate-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable

        - name: ptp-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable

        - name: sriov-network-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable

        - name: lvms-operator
          channels:
            - name: stable-4.19

        - name: cluster-logging
          channels:
            - name: stable-6.4

  helm: {}


---

🚀 How To Run

oc mirror --config imageset-config.yaml docker://bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443


---

🔍 After Mirror (IMPORTANT)

Re-apply catalog:

oc apply -f cs-redhat-operator-index-v4-19.yaml


---

✅ Verify (VERY IMPORTANT)

oc get packagemanifest -n openshift-marketplace | grep odf

👉 Must show ALL:

odf-operator

odf-dependencies

mcg-operator

rook-ceph

cephcsi



---

⚠️ Important Notes

1️⃣ No release images = only operator upgrade possible

❌ Cannot upgrade cluster

✅ Can upgrade operators



---

2️⃣ Why we still list all ODF packages

👉 In disconnected setup:

> OLM does NOT auto-fetch dependencies from internet



So you must include:

dependencies

metadata

images



